{
  "texts": [
    "Moreover, anthropomorphism is closely related to discussions of agency, human exceptionalism, and subjectivity (Bennett, 2010; Hodder, 2012; Latour, 2014).",
    "There is a rich literature on the implications of anthropomorphism in relation to biology and the natural world (Karadimas, 2012; DeMello, 2021; Hathaway, 2022).",
    "Also, feminist studies of science and technology have long leveraged anthropomorphism in their challenging of the dominant values and traditional boundaries between subject and object in science (Haraway, 1988; Longino, 1990; Suchman, 2008; Harding, 2013).",
    "ANTHROSCORE enables engagement with these topics using a quantitative lens.",
    "Our analysis is limited to English data, where thirdperson singular pronouns mark animacy."
  ]
}